The paper deals with deep neural networks for semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task, and proposes an approach for unsupervised domain adaptation (UDA) using semi-supervised learning methods. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of entropy minimization, which is a popular approach in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper deals with class imbalance, which is a common issue in natural language processing and falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper presents experiments on synthetic-to-real and cross-city adaptation, which are related to multimedia and fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
